# /etc/fw_env.config — libubootenv (fw_setenv/fw_printenv)
# mtd4 holds two redundant 128KB U-Boot env copies on Zynq Antminer NAND
# (am1-s9 and am2-s17 share the same partition layout).
# Format: <device> <offset> <env_size> <flash_sector_size> <num_sectors>
# Flash sector = 128KB (NAND erase block on Micron MT29F2G08ABAEAWP).
#
# GEOMETRY VERIFIED against a real on-flash dump (2026-06-05,
# output/nand-backup-135-20260605/mtd4_uboot_env.b64, 524288 B):
#   - copy A @ 0x00000, copy B @ 0x20000 (matches below);
#   - ENV_SIZE = 0x20000 — CRC32 over data[5:0x20000] matches the stored
#     header CRC for BOTH copies exactly (a smaller ENV_SIZE does NOT match,
#     so the size is right and U-Boot's CONFIG_ENV_SIZE is 0x20000);
#   - redundant header = crc32(4, little-endian) + flags(1); NAND incremental
#     flag scheme (copy A flags=0x04, copy B flags=0x05 -> B newer/active).
# So the OFFSETS and ENV_SIZE are correct. The S99upgrade clear-failure on the
# live S9 was a write/verify-logic bug (two non-atomic fw_setenv calls + a
# single readback on weak-ECC mtd4), NOT a geometry mismatch — fixed in
# S99upgrade (atomic --script transaction + retry + per-attempt verify).
# Do NOT "fix" this by shrinking ENV_SIZE or by raw-nandwrite (load-bearing
# feedback_am2_uboot_env_flip_must_use_fw_setenv).
/dev/mtd4   0x00000   0x20000   0x20000   1
/dev/mtd4   0x20000   0x20000   0x20000   1
